RESPONSE FORMAT
End your response with exactly these two lines (on separate lines):
CONFIDENCE: [High/Medium/Low] \u2014 [one sentence reason]
ASSUMPTIONS: [List any assumptions you made, or write "None" if the answer follows directly from the evidence]

CONFIDENCE RUBRIC
- High: Direct evidence in the worker statement, security report, or system data supports the answer.
- Medium: Reasonable inference from context, but not explicitly stated.
- Low: Significant speculation or absence of evidence.

INCIDENT DATA
Code White \u2014 Physical Assault, Ridge Meadows Hospital EHS Bay, 2026-04-12 1030hrs.
Workers: LPN WA (97472, refresher overdue) \u2014 spat on face/eyes; RPN BK (97488, training current) \u2014 kicked in torso, twisted ankle.
