4. Workers Affected (training status, injuries, return-to-work)
5. Evidence Reviewed
6. Contributing Factors (by category, with ratings)
7. Root/Systemic Causes
8. Corrective Actions (table format: Action | Type | Owner | Priority | Status)
9. Outstanding Items / Follow-up Required
10. Manager Sign-Off [Placeholder]

Use professional, trauma-informed language. Label all inferences. Flag any cross-source discrepancies.`,

  'evidence':()=>`You are a workplace violence investigation assistant. Analyze all available evidence for this investigation and surface contradictions, gaps, and points requiring clarification.

INCIDENT
Code White, Ridge Meadows Hospital EHS Bay, 2026-04-12 1030hrs.
WA spat on face/eyes; BK kicked in torso, twisted ankle.

EVIDENCE SOURCES
Security report: ${INC.sec}
WA statement: ${INC.workers[0].stmt}
BK statement: ${INC.workers[1].stmt}
Context: Unit over capacity, short-staffed. WA refresher overdue. Patient had prior Code White with no indicator applied.

PRODUCE THREE SECTIONS

1. CONTRADICTIONS OR DISCREPANCIES
List any places where two sources tell different stories or suggest different timelines. If none, say so explicitly.

2. EVIDENCE GAPS
List what should have been captured but isn't present. What's missing that would strengthen this investigation?

3. POINTS REQUIRING CLARIFICATION
List specific questions the investigator should follow up on \u2014 with whom, and why.

Be direct. Cite specific sources. If the evidence is consistent and complete, say so clearly.
Header: AI EVIDENCE ANALYSIS \u2014 MANAGER REVIEW REQUIRED.`,
};

async function runAI(type,outId){
  const out=document.getElementById(outId);if(!out)return;
  out.innerHTML=`<div class="loading"><div class="spinner"></div>Generating \u2014 synthesizing all inputs\u2026</div>`;
  const maxTokens = type==='summary' ? 2500 : type==='evidence' ? 1500 : 1600;
  try{
    const r=await fetch('https://api.anthropic.com/v1/messages',{method:'POST',headers:{'Content-Type':'application/json'},
      body:JSON.stringify({model:AI_MODEL,max_tokens:maxTokens,messages:[{role:'user',content:PROMPTS[type]()}]})});
    const d=await r.json();
    const txt=d.content?.[0]?.text||'No response.';
    out.innerHTML=`<div class="ai-box"><div class="ai-hdr">&#10022; AI draft \u2014 ${AI_MODEL_LABEL}<button class="btn btn-ghost btn-xs" style="margin-left:auto" onclick="navigator.clipboard.writeText(this.closest('.ai-box').querySelector('textarea').value).then(()=>toast('Copied','s'))">Copy</button></div><textarea rows="${type==='summary'?28:14}">${txt}</textarea></div>`;
    toast('AI draft ready \u2014 review before using','w');
  }catch(e){out.innerHTML=`<div style="color:var(--red);font-size:12px;padding:8px 0">Error: ${e.message}</div>`;}
}

/* ── MODALS ── */
function showComplete(){document.getElementById('complete-modal').classList.add('show');}
function confirmComplete(){document.getElementById('complete-modal').classList.remove('show');toast('Investigation complete \u2014 export ready for Web IIT','s');setTimeout(()=>showView('dash'),700);}

/* ── TOAST ── */
function toast(msg,type='i'){
  const d=document.createElement('div');d.className=`toast t-${type}`;d.textContent=msg;
  document.getElementById('toasts').appendChild(d);setTimeout(()=>d.remove(),3200);
}

/* ── INIT ── */
showView('dash');
</script>
